node.text: How do I properly thank you all? I’m speechless...my sister surprised me with this montage of videos from all of you!! How did you all pull this surprise???? Today was the most special birthday celebration because of all of you and also my amazing family! I’m truly blessed beyond words. I’ll forever remember today! Thank you so so so much!!!

node.text: To any woman doubting herself right now, this message is for you. This girl in this picture is me… Lebanese, Born and raised in Congo, Africa, I moved to the US with dreams and determination and with lots of hope. What I found myself doing is going into a career choice that would offer me “ security “ ( lawyer) but never offered me fullfillment. Midway through, I fell in a funk and ultimately faced the feeling of self loss. Uncertainty crept in, a big void in my life and in my heart weighed on me heavily. It took over and dominated. How can you go through life feeling so empty? So I did something for myself that scared the heck out of me. I took a chance on ME. I stepped away from school and a career choice that was a safety net and stepped into a journey that had no map, no direction and filled with bumps, pot holes, mountains, hills. All I could do was believe in myself, my resilience, my new commitment to do what makes my heart happy. I took that step, which led to another. I walked, jogged and then hit that road running. Through the bumps, and climbing mountains, I looked around me with a smile on my face and joy in my heart as I enjoyed the beautiful views that small victories offered me along the way. This road was not an easy one, but it has made me wiser, stronger and more motivated then ever to keep rising and achieving my goals. Here we are. 50,000 SQ FT warehouse behind me with my logo on it. A dream that has come true which humbles me to the core. When I drive up to our warehouse everyday, it’s a constant reminder of what I fought for to get here. It’s a reminder of my family who were my rock through it all and this community that uplifts me with your support every day. So my friend, look at this picture and may it be a reminder to you that YOU can do it too. Never doubt yourself, never let fear hold you back. Take a chance on yourself, believe in yourself and commit to making your dreams a reality. Be patient, remember things don’t happen overnight. Celebrate the small victories, stay humble and do what you do with heart and compassion. And if you have naysayers around you, let it ignite the fire in you to prove them wrong. With Love, Farah.
